    <div class="AssessmentProblem.identifier">102755</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.type">ShortAnswerResponse</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.statement"><p>Mai is making personal pizzas. For 4 pizzas, she uses 10&#xA0;ounces of cheese.</p>

<div class="imgrid">
<div class="g--row g--row-1">
<div class="g--column g--two-third g--content g--col-1 g--row-1">
<table border="1">
	<thead>
		<tr>
			<th scope="col">number&#xA0;of&#xA0;pizzas</th>
			<th scope="col">ounces&#xA0;of&#xA0;cheese</th>
		</tr>
	</thead>
	<tbody>
		<tr>
			<td>4</td>
			<td>10</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td></td>
			<td></td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td></td>
			<td></td>
		</tr>
	</tbody>
</table>
</div>

<div class="g--column g--one-third g--content g--col-2 g--row-1">
<p>a.&#xA0;How much cheese does Mai use per pizza?</p>

<p>b. At this rate, how much cheese will she need to make 15 pizzas?</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.solution"><p>Mai uses 2.5 ounces of cheese per pizza, because <span class="math math-repaired" data-png-file-id="47629">\(10 \div 4 = 2.5\)</span>. She will need 37.5 ounces of cheese for 15 pizzas, because&#xA0;<span class="math math-repaired" data-png-file-id="47666">\(2.5 \boldcdot 15=37.5\)</span>.</p>
</div>
